    summary: "My search did not directly lead to a LinkedIn profile with the exact URL \"linkedin.com/in/sameer-mohammad-19743b286\". However, it returned several individuals named Sameer Mohammad with different professional backgrounds and affiliations, some of whom have LinkedIn presences or related professional profiles.\n\nHere\'s a summary of the findings:\n\n*   **Sameer F. Mohammad (Instructor at UAEU):** An instructor in the Electrical Engineering Department at the United Arab Emirates University (UAEU), born in Kuwait in 1971. He holds B.Sc. (1994) and M.Sc. (2010) degrees in electrical power engineering from Yarmouk University. His interests include power system operation and optimization, power system restructuring, reactive power pricing, control, and electrical machines. He previously worked at Yarmouk University, National Electric Power Company (NEPCO), and the Water and Electricity Department (WED) in Abu Dhabi.[1]\n*   **Sameer Mohammad (Data Systems and Web Applications):** A professional focused on data engineering, analytics, and full-stack development, with experience across full-stack development, APIs, SQL-backed systems, and product delivery. His portfolio mentions building data systems and modern web applications, including CRM platform features and EMR platform modules.[2]\n*   **Sameer Mohammad (Scientist/Researcher):** This Sameer Mohammad is listed on ORCID with employment history including King Abdullah International Medical Research Center (Scientist/Principal Investigator since 2014), Weill Cornell Medicine (Research Associate/Instructor of Biochemistry from 2008-2014), and University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences (Postdoctoral Fellow from 2005-2008).[3] He has co-authored several journal articles on topics such as obesity, metabolic research, and proteotoxic stress response.[3] One publication also identifies him as being from the Department of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology, University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences.[4]\n*   **Sameer Mohammad (Frontend Developer):** This individual has a frontend developer portfolio. He has a Bachelor\'s in Computer Applications from Bharathi Degree College (2021-2024) and is passionate about creating clean and responsive websites. His skills include HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Java, Selenium, Tailwind CSS, and Bootstrap, and he has built projects like a Currency Converter and a Spotify Clone.[5]\n\nSources:\n[1] [uaeu.ac.ae](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHR_-VSXabdtZ4i6_SoDBO06wf7256byEOvt10HgpwZaAgxO36ex_0xOP3o7tOfUdxPPDkaRTryQ59jNzNnpKvThZWx7i902fXfRnIVfWmLKj_v5sfD_2RY3_xbBBIrFBQMra-a_iXe0P14yzN4Ou1_qYjsV_h0vJC70p24bRh_0X7FZw==)\n[2] [sameerion.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGHj5UYIv81QX4_Vbotq7isR5zqX2yW1oPDkQW726nl-s_c8sGNUi9snttiWxFvfbki-OX34Hc_PfzBkJBteAKwB5f4_h3oXFPjzwxfDJ2v1AgY4IM=)\n[3] [orcid.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEZOJ4I9yptctgaG2CWzExR_P-DBUc3pLu54WqYcJxUfm4ge-zHH5qn0gPHoGoSnrg5MSEPsUBWAcV1mCdpi7B-udKv3t5mRU0tPpprwStJDFdwn7CaqyfhdpfmUdWT3g==)\n[4] [nih.gov](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHjHVTa0VugUc4px7W4inVq3_LmG1KQGmc0wtbF1dlRYMvZVOqujeaOHVcJNfJZhUKaADoNTRz8r1_-sd27KasCGTSiVddjDF3uD7Vcg0GUAhRSyOEP7QV3yRNCeV9OrXcUd4INGD63T0rpPw==)\n[5] [github.io](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH8FwYfVXwIdHD--OT9jrA0sfC3TQ-xDa74nSeDgylmES-3-HNKDOf90IUo2hCuJtualkAvzkw4V8CYNemu70Io7PVY8oKID_DdEGL_o9_byPugeOCAANHQF3Sb65HoMZAMEbL6CecX)"
