full-stack proficiency. I\'m also preparing for the next step.\n\n\n**Refining Website Requirements**\n\nNow I\'m clarifying the website specifications! I must ensure Sameer\'s portfolio reflects a clean, minimalist design with fluid animations and responsiveness, modeled after Nabyendu Ojha\'s site. It should contain \"Projects,\" \"Resume,\" and \"Contact\" sections, and should be a single-page React application with smooth scrolling navigation.\n\n\n**Confirming Site Structure**\n\nI\'m now determining Nabyendu\'s portfolio layout, focusing on single-page, scrolling structure. I\'m noting the common high-contrast typography and standard sections (About, Skills, Projects, Experience, Contact). I am double checking packages and dependencies from earlier, and it looks like it\'s all ready to go. I just checked the dependencies and it has lucide-react and motion! Let\'s check the code and compile and see what files are already there!\n\n\n**Updating Metadata Configuration**\n\nI\'m now going to update the `metadata.json` file. Following the instructions, I\'ll add a name and description, because they are currently empty. I\'ll make the updates based on the current context, ensuring I\'m following the instructions\' specific naming guidelines for this type of application. I will focus on making it the right name.\n\n\n"
