  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Navbar Options**\n\nI\'m now contemplating Nabyendu\'s typical navbar designs, specifically for the `/src/components/Navbar.tsx` file. I\'m recalling a fixed, blurred-background style, a minimalist left-aligned approach, and a sticky header with a centered capsule. I\'m trying to decide which would be most fitting for the project.\n\n\n**Deciding on Navigation Style**\n\nI\'ve decided on a sticky, capsule-style navbar with a subtle blur, light border, and shadow. It will sit at the top, a modern and minimalist design. I will use `lucide-react` icons for the nav options that scroll to \"About,\" \"Projects,\" \"Resume,\" and \"Contact\" sections. I\'m now leaning toward a single, polished theme, as the guide suggests avoiding unnecessary complexity.\n\n\n**Choosing the Theme**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the app\'s overall aesthetics. I\'m torn between a sleek light theme and a premium dark one, each with minimalist elements. A light theme with dark accents, or a modern \"Slate & Canvas\" dark theme are strong contenders. I\'m leaning toward a polished dark theme because it feels tech-forward and developer-centric. I\'ll check Nabyendu\'s portfolio for inspiration.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create the `/src/components/Navbar.tsx` component. It will feature a minimalist, floating glassmorphism capsule design that sticks to the top of the viewport. It will have smooth active tab indicators powered by `motion/react` and a mobile-friendly hamburger menu for seamless responsiveness."
