  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Verifying Complete Success**\n\nI\'m incredibly pleased to report a fully successful build! Now, I\'m shifting focus to ensuring thoroughness. I need to make sure I haven\'t overlooked any crucial files. Hold on, I\'m also going to circle back and re-evaluate the user request, noting the specific criteria laid out for design elements.\n\n\n**Analyzing Design Requirements**\n\nI\'m now diving into the design phase and have started extracting required details for the layout. I\'m taking information from the provided LinkedIn profile to build feature sections. I\'m focusing on project, resume, and contact information sections, but I\'m thinking of how to best integrate them, too. I\'ve finished reviewing the previous build and I\'m very excited about the possibilities!\n\n\n**Defining Project Integration**\n\nI\'m now integrating the project grid with filters and modal overlays for detailed views. I\'m focusing on showcasing challenge summaries and tech stacks. I\'m also preparing for the interactive resume section, including competence metrics and print functionality. Plus, the contact hub design and scroll-to-top are ready. Everything looks solid, I\'m now just reviewing files to ensure everything built correctly.\n\n\n**Reviewing Feature Implementation**\n\nI\'ve just confirmed that the `Navbar`, `Hero`, `Projects`, `Experience`, `Resume`, `Contact`, and `Footer` components are all functional, working as expected to deliver the user experience. The `App` component binds everything responsively into a dynamic template. Also, `index.css` is handling crucial styling, including responsive prints.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and implemented a highly polished, responsive, and minimalist portfolio website for you, taking inspiration from the clean, developer-centric design of **Nabyendu Ojha\'s portfolio** and integrating your professional details from **LinkedIn**.\n\nThe application compiles and builds successfully with native TypeScript type-safety. Below is a structured summary of the design choices and interactive sections:\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Design Identity\n*   **Slate & Emerald Dark Theme**: Styled with a high-contrast dark palette (`bg-zinc-950`) combined with subtle charcoal card panels, soft gray borders, and emerald (`emerald-400`) and indigo accents.\n*   **Premium Typography**: Imported and paired **Space Grotesk** for display-level headers and section markers, **Inter** for legible UI and body content, and **JetBrains Mono** for status flags and code blocks.\n*   **Fluid Responsiveness & Micro-interactions**: Fully optimized for mobile, tablet, and desktop viewing, enhanced with hover transitions, interactive modal overlays, and custom-styled webkit scrollbars.\n\n---\n\n### \360\237\247\261 Completed Features & Sections\n\n1.  **Floating Navigation Capsule (`Navbar`)**\n    *   Features a compact floating glassmorphism capsule that anchors to the top of the viewport.\n    *   Registers an **Intersection Observer API** that tracks scroll coordinates automatically, highlighting active nav items with smooth sliding spring transitions.\n    *   Includes a responsive drawer menu for mobile touch targets.\n\n2.  **Split-Screen Interactive Intro (`Hero`)**\n    *   **Left Column**: High-impact typographic introduction, availability pill, brief biography, and quick navigation triggers.\n    *   **Right Column**: An interactive, custom-styled **Mock IDE console card** containing an object definition of your core developer persona with syntax-highlighted TypeScript.\n\n3.  **Filtered Project Directory (`Projects`)**\n    *   Renders a modular catalog of your development works.\n    *   Includes **interactive filtering tabs** (All, Full-Stack, Frontend, AI) to organize your projects instantly.\n    *   Cards feature direct links to live deployments and GitHub repositories, alongside an **interactive \"View Details\" button** that launches a modal overlay explaining technical hurdles and architecture.\n\n4.  **Career & Academic Milestones (`Experience`)**\n    *   A split vertical timeline structure highlighting **Work History** on one side and **Education & Certifications** on the other.\n    *   Presents company milestones, duration tags, and structured bullet points highlighting accomplishments, finished with verify links for industry credentials.\n\n5.  **Interactive A4 CV Sheet & Skill Matrix (`Resume`)**\n    *   **Skill progression gauges** track competence scores with staggered viewport enter animations.\n    *   **Virtual Resume Sheet**: A paper-like document centered on a charcoal frame, outlining contact cards, summary bios, experience, and academic roots.\n    *   **One-Click Print/PDF**: Integrates custom **CSS `@media print` directives** to generate a clean, high-contrast, black-and-white print output when printing or saving as a PDF from the browser.\n\n6.  **Secure Communication Hub (`Contact` & `Footer`)**\n    *   Includes a fully-validated React message dispatcher form with a live processing spinner and an animated confirmation slide.\n    *   Displays fast direct communication links (direct email and social media profile badges).\n    *   The footer closes with a dynamic copyright stamp and a scroll-to-top accelerator.\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 5
      nanos: 575949324
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
